<p>As seasons change, so do consumer shopping preferences, and retailers need to keep pace with those shifts heading into the festive sales period. This is the time of year when consumers begin turning attention toward holiday shopping and Black Friday deals, which makes it a good moment for retailers to assess their own efficiency, capability, and service level and identify where they can improve to drive sales.</p>

<h2>End-of-summer sales and clearance</h2>
<p>As evenings get cooler and winter approaches, shoppers begin refreshing their wardrobes, and retailers need to clear space for new stock. Personalized end-of-summer discounts help encourage customers to pick up last-minute items at more affordable prices. Teamwork Commerce's real-time Analytics and Reporting tool gives retailers visibility into live store performance, inventory, and on-demand KPI reports, so they can better understand operational needs and consumer preferences when building those offers. Staying on top of inventory management during this transition, with complete visibility of stock and accurate monitoring as end-of-summer sales clear space, helps retailers move seasonal stock confidently while minimizing waste.</p>

<h2>Black Friday footfall</h2>
<p>Black Friday remains one of the biggest dates on the retail calendar. According to Statista, almost two-thirds of UK consumers planned to spend across Black Friday and Cyber Weekend in 2023, with £3.9 billion expected to be spent in stores that year alone. To make the most of that footfall, retailers need to streamline processes and deliver a seamless experience during the surge. Teamwork Commerce's Mobile POS uses cloud-based technology to centralize and streamline stored data, giving staff the ability to handle customer queries and complete transactions from anywhere on the shop floor, a useful queue-busting tool during an otherwise chaotic period. RFID-powered self-checkout adds to this by letting shoppers scan their own items at their own pace, reducing human error and optimizing checkout times to help stores handle more transactions during peak hours.</p>

<h2>Hybrid holiday shopping</h2>
<p>The Christmas season shortly follows Black Friday, and according to Deloitte, shoppers planned to spend more at Christmas in 2023 than they did the year before, while continuing to prioritize savings. Consumers increasingly blend the convenience of online shopping with in-store browsing, so retailers need omnichannel solutions that let staff deliver strong experiences across both. Teamwork's real-time analytics can surface buyer purchase history to help staff provide more relevant, personalized service, while Teamwork's Omnichannel Order Management System keeps online orders and in-store transactions streamlined from a single cloud-based system. That includes support for Buy Online Pickup In-Store and Buy Online Return In-Store, giving customers quick, low-effort ways to process returns and exchanges whether they're shopping in-store or online.</p>

<h2>The takeaway</h2>
<p>Retailers should use the next few months to look closely at their current processes and see what can be improved. Staying on top of stock availability, order management, and customer needs should be a priority through year-end, positioning retailers to close out 2024 strong and start 2025 from a position of strength.</p>
